The paper discusses the use of deep learning techniques in machine health monitoring, which involves processing and analyzing big machinery data. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given the focus on deep learning techniques, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CV, cs.NE, and cs.SY.
